    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "**Problem**\n\nOpening any file handled by the tailwindcss LSP (e.g. TypeScript, TSX, HTML) causes a multi-second UI freeze on first attach. The freeze scales with project size.\n\n**Root cause**\n\ntailwindcss.lua defines find_tailwind_global_css() which is called synchronously inside before_init. It uses vim.fs.find with limit = math.huge to recursively scan the entire project tree for CSS/SCSS/PCSS files, reading each one to find an @import \"tailwindcss\" statement:\n\n```lua\n local files = vim.fs.find(function(name)\n   return name:match(\"%.css$\") or name:match(\"%.scss$\") or name:match(\"%.pcss$\")\n end, {\n   path = root,\n   type = \"file\",\n   limit = math.huge, -- search full tree  ← the problem\n })\n```\n\nBecause root_dir falls back to .git for Tailwind v4 projects, the scan root is the git repository root, which typically includes node_modules and other large directories.\n\nThis blocks Neovim's main loop for the entire duration of the scan.\n\n**Expected behavior**\n\nFile open should not freeze. We should use a non-blocking approach or skip folders like node_modules. \n\n**Possible fix**\n\nReplace the blocking file scan with async scan or don't scan folders that are listed in the .gitignore file. Not sure if using `git`  cli is wanted. But `git ls-files` could help a lot. \n\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-05T14:33:05Z",
