            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@oedotme ohh I see. The native lsp detection does according to official docs:\n\n> For Tailwind CSS v4: The extension scans your project for CSS files and determines the \"root\" CSS file.\n> For Tailwind CSS v3 (and earlier): The extension automatically uses the first tailwind.config.{js,cjs,mjs,ts,cts,mts} file it finds.\n\nDo you know if it is efficient? (Ignoring node_modules)? Or at least async. It is definitely the better way I guess. I guess we can close this issue and the related PR as soon as we have progress on yours. ",
